      "ingredients": "<ul>\n<li><span>Oils:</span> hazelnut oil, grape seed oil, rice oil (we use light oils that do not clog pores and normalize the sebaceous glands)</ li >\n<li><span>Water</span></li>\n<li><span>Active ingredients:</span> triglycerides (to reduce moisture loss), ceramides (to restore the lipid layer of the skin), olive squalane (for a healing and rejuvenating effect), methylsulfonylmethane (blocks collagen adhesion, heals, has an anti-inflammatory effect), vitamin B3 (for pigmentation reduction, collagen synthesis, improvement of elasticity), fucus extract (relieves swelling, enhances lymph flow), provitamin B5 (panthenol is a soothing and skin-healing component), allantoin (promotes skin regeneration), bisabolol (regenerates and soothes the skin), synthetic urea (moisturizing ingredient), hyaluronic acid (moisturizing ingredient), vitamin C (protects against damage caused by excessive UV radiation, increases collagen production, fights acne-causing bacteria, reduces pigmentation and rosacea), CO2 rosemary extract (antioxidant, prevents skin aging), zinc oxide (heals)</li>\n<li><span>Essential oils:</span> mandarin, litsea and lemongrass</li>\n<li><span>Emulsifiers:</span> cetearyl olivate, sorbitan olivate, cetearyl alcohol, cetearyl glucoside (safe natural emulsifiers - connectors of the water and oil phases in the cream)</li>\n<li><span>Preservatives:</span> sorbic acid (natural preservative), benzoic acid (natural preservative), dehydracetic acid (natural preservative), benzyl alcohol (natural preservative), CO2 rosemary extract (antioxidant)</li>\n</ul>",
      "shortDescription": "To restore a lipid layer, let's take triglycerides, ceramides, squalene and create a cream based on the light oils of rice seeds, hazelnuts and grape seed. Methylsulfonylmethane, allantoin, algae extracts, vitamins B3 and B5 will help us strengthen the protective function of your skin. <aside>We will boost the regeneration process with vitamin C and add moisturizing to your skin using synthetic urea (a natural moisturiser) and hyaluronic acid. The last but not the least, litsey, mandarin and lemongrass oils will help the ingredients get deeper into your skin to nourish and balance it out.</aside>",
