      "ingredients": "<ul>\n<li>\n<span>Oils:</span> wheat germ, green coffee, argan, rice</li>\n<li><span>Neroli flower water</span></li>\n<li><span>Active ingredients:</span> triglycerides, ceramides, olive squalene, methylsulfonylmethane, vitamin B3, fucus extract, provitamin B5 (panthenol), allantoin, bisabolol, urea, hyaluronic acid, vitamin C, palmitol tripeptide-38, antarcticin</li>\n<li><span>Essential oils:</span> neroli</li>\n<li><span>Emulsifiers:</span> cetearyl olivate, sorbitan olivate, cetearyl alcohol, cetearyl glucoside (safe natural emulsifiers - connectors of the water and oil phases in the cream)</li>\n<li><span>Preservatives:</span> propanediol (natural preservative), benzoic acid (natural preservative), sorbitan caprylate (natural preservative), citric acid (natural preservative), potasium sorbate (natural preservative), sodium benzoate (natural preservative), CO2 rosemary extract (antioxidant)</li>\n</ul>",
      "shortDescription": "Your answers indicated that you would like to reduce the depth of wrinkles and moisturise your skin. To achieve this, we will take neroli hydrolat as the water base of the cream, add the oils of rice, argan, green coffee and wheat germ, squalene and triglycerides with ceramides - they will strengthen the lipid layer of your skin. <aside>Vitamins C, B3 and B5 will increase firmness and elasticity, while hyaluronic acid and two types of peptides will help to produce collagen, fibronectin and hyaluronic acid - and your skin will glow again!</aside>",
